Don't forget that Florida has many natural springs to explore! These two springs are located about 1hr away from Panama City Beach or Destin. Ponce De Leon Springs- it's $4 per vehicle to get into the park and It's open from 8am until sunset all year. The spring water is 68 degrees Fahrenheit all year round so it is chilly! I saw people bring tubes with umbrellas to float around here and thought that was such a good idea! There are nature trails you can walk around as well. Morrison Springs County Park- this spot is near Ponce De Leon and has more of a natural feel to it. It's a popular spot for diving and even has a small cave divers can go into! This is a great spot to kayak too. It includes a diving dock, boat ramp, and boardwalks. It's free to visit! This was my favorite thing we did on our last Florida trip!
